	<h1 class="pages-title">What is TritonMUN?</h1>
    <p class = "pages-description">
	  Triton Model United Nations is the name of the home conference series hosted by MUN at UCSD. The conference is entirely run by UCSD students who are committed to bringing global topics to the local community by providing the opportunity for students to practice diplomacy, networking, and public speaking.
	</p>
    <p class = "pages-description">
      Every year, our team puts on two conferences: a one-day fall conference, and a two-day spring conference. The aim of each conference is to expose students to key international issues, build students’ public speaking skills and help them to understand different social, political and economic perspectives. We believe that in doing so, we help build a more perceptive and understanding generation.
    </p>
    <p class = "pages-description">
      Over the past few years, our TritonMUN team has been enthusiastically growing to unprecedented heights. In addition to our expanding high school conferences, new branches of our club are developing plans to host our first-ever collegiate conference and a joint conference with the United Nations Association, San Diego. Contact us at <a href = "mailto:tritonmun.ucsd@gmail.com">tritonmun.ucsd@gmail.com</a> or visit our Contact Us page for more information.
